    "caption": "The world's smallest bear has the world's longest tongue for the job.",
    "shortDescription": "Sun bears live in the rainforests of Southeast Asia and are the smallest bear species — roughly the size of a large dog. They have jet-black fur with a pale crescent chest patch that gives them their name, and an extraordinarily long tongue — up to twenty-five centimetres — that they use to extract honey from beehives and termites from mounds. Fun fact: Sun bears have the longest tongue relative to body size of any bear."
